<br>
Your choices are human, erudite, dark elf, high elf, and gnome.<br>
<br>
Humans -- good around overall, blind as bats at night (but at 16 its a nonissue, and at 29, don't sweat it.  If you are not wearing a robe, people will always think you are a monk.  No mage library nearby, so you have to hit Akanon, Erudin, or Neriak for summoning spellage.  The race that is the most neutral, factionwise.<br>
<br>
Erudite -- Best INT, blind, yawner of a newbie zone.  Library nearby.<br>
<br>
Dark Elf -- second best INT, vision is great, library in your home city.  Bad thing... everyone hates you, and if you try to get faction with any other group to buy spells outside of neriak, the necros will KOS you when you return, and one of these KOS'ing necros is right outside the place where you go to buy spells.  Newbie zone just plain chomps.<br>
If you see any decaying skellies, kill them, sell the stacks of bone chips to necros for inflated prices, for spells.<br>
<br>
Gnomes -- Library, decent newbie zone, infravision... only downside is that ogres keep mistaking you for a footstool, or lunch.  Sometimes its hard to pop off a bolt spell because you have line of sight problems with hills.  Factionwise, you are pretty neutral (assuming agnostic -- this can change if you chose a deity).<br>
<br>
High elves -- newbie zone is overpopulated -- get a bind in Kaladim and hunt in butcherblock, infravision, second lowest INT next to humans (but high WIS and CHA that are both good things when soloing).  Your strength isn't great -- you will hit like a baby in melee, but after 24, melee is suicide anyway if soloing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalamos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(1/17/01 5:20:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What race?</span><hr size=1> Well ... Cendienoflanys (nice name by the way) summed it up as good as it can be done.  I do feel though that when it comes to picking a race for a Mage, it's more about the roleplaying aspect rather than the base starting stats.  I chose a High Elf because I like being tall (I'm already kind of a shorty in real life so Gnomes weren't appealing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and I like the look of them.  I put 25 points into Int and the other 5 into Str so I could carry more crap (HIEs are frail as a toothpick).  Any weakness in stats can be made up in items.<br>
<br>
The other choice for me would have been a DE Mage but I decided I didn't want to be KOS in most of the world and all my friends play &quot;good&quot; races.  I say when it comes to a Mage, a class that could probably lvl up to 50 naked thanks to our pets, pick a race based your playstyle ... stats can be tweaked later with equipment.<br>
<br>
Kalamos Darksummons<br>
45th Magician<br>
The Seventh Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uamorsaylnn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amorsaylnn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(1/18/01 2:39:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What race?</span><hr size=1> I play an agnostic dark elf magician.  I am not KoS in Qeynos (including priesthoods) or Freeport, though I did do a bit of faction works with the Karana bandits and, earlier, orcs over in the Commonlands.  I am KoS in Halas, halfling areas, and nearly all of the Odus and Fay, but aside from some sneaking to Unrest or Mistmoore (haven't been to Kedge yet), I'm content.  I like the look, statistics, and it provides some interesting RP ideas... I play Amorsaylnn as an exiled Teir'dal who makes her home in Qeynos.<br>
<br>
