<i>Elementalist of the 51st Summoning<br></i></body>
<body text=0/200/50><b>Tunare's Servant on Fennin Ro</b></body><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uamorsaylnn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amorsaylnn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/18/01 4:34:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What race?</span><hr size=1> I like Verant's original intent for Qeynos, but that's the stance of a role-player.  In game terms, it is out of the way (in vicinity to useful dungeons and teleport spots) and not very populated.  There is more than one way to play a mage, and I don't believe there is a &quot;best&quot; race.  Some races may be easier to play than others.<br>
<br>
~Amorsaylnn Frost &lt;Winterborne&gt;<br>
